HEADWORD: Epigrammatist
<hw>Ep`i*gram"ma*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>epigrammatista</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧pigrammatiste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who composes epigrams,
or makes use of them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brisk <qex>epigrammatist</qex> showing off his own
cleverness.</q> <rj><qau>Holmes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epigrammatize</ent>⟦br⟧
